\begin_layout Standard
The heteroscedastic envelope model 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "su2012estimation"

\end_inset

 is used when the data has none constant error structure, and it is developed
 under the framework of estimating multivariate means for different populations.
 To use the heteroscedastic envelope model, the number of response should
 be greater than or equal to the number of populations.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The standard model for estimating multivariate means for 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

