\begin_layout Standard
The computing of the envelope models involve Grassmann manifold optimization.
 The package sg_min 2.4.1 by Ross Lippert (http://web.mit.edu/
\begin_inset Formula $\sim$
\end_inset

ripper/www.sgmin.html) uses the analytical first derivative and numerical
 second derivative of the objective function, and we find it very stable.
 The Grassmann manifold optimization in this package is then based on sg_min
 2.4.1.
 Because of the iterative nature of the optimization, we offer some optional
 arguments so that the users can control the convergence tolerance and speed,
 as well as monitoring the iteration process.
 In functions 
\family typewriter
modelselectaic
\family default
, 
\family typewriter
modelselectbic
\family default
, 
\family typewriter
modelselectlrt
\family default
, 
\family typewriter
env
\family default
, 
\family typewriter
henv
\family default
, 
\family typewriter
ienv
\family default
, 
\family typewriter
penv
\family default
, 
\family typewriter
senv
\family default
, 
\family typewriter
xenv
\family default
 and 
\family typewriter
bootstrapse
\family default
, there is an optional input argument 
\family typewriter
Opts
\family default
.
 Opts is a list, which has five elements: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Opts.maxIter: This controls the maximum number of iterations.
 The default value is 
\begin_inset Formula $300$
\end_inset

.
 The iterations will terminate once the maximum number of iterations is
 reached, then the results are based on the last iteration.
 At the same time, a warning 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\family typewriter
WARNING: reached maximum number of iterations without convergence for specified
 tolerances
\family default
 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

is printed out.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Opts.ftol: This controls the tolerance parameter of the objective function.
 The default value is 
\begin_inset Formula $1e-10$
\end_inset

.
 The iteration will terminate once the tolerance condition for both the
 objective function and its derivative are reached.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Opts.gradtol: This controls the tolerance parameter of the derivative of
 the objective function.
 The default value is 
\begin_inset Formula $1e-7$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

